Definition. Niphatidae with a paratangential ectosomal reticulation of fibers or tracts, obscured by the conulose surface produced by ends of primary longitudinal fibers (
Desqueyroux-Faúndez & Valentine 2002
).

Type species.
Niphates erecta
Duchassaing & Michelotti, 1864
(by subsequent designation;
Wiedenmayer 1977
).

Spicules. Oxeas ( 155–270 / 7–18 µm). Slightly curved, smooth, stylote and strongylote forms are present (
Fig. 5
). Juveniles may be smaller and thinner ( 100 / 3 µm).
